Mary-Louise Parker -LRB- born August 2 , 1964 -RRB- is an American actress and author .
In addition to her many films , Parker enjoyed great popularity for her lead role on Showtime 's television series Weeds portraying Nancy Botwin , for which she received the Golden Globe Award for Best Actress in 2006 .
Parker has appeared in films and series including RED , RED 2 , Fried Green Tomatoes , Boys on the Side , The West Wing , and Angels in America , for which she received a Golden Globe and an Emmy Award for Best Supporting Actress .
Parker is also the recipient of the 2001 Tony Award for Best Actress for her performance in the Broadway play Proof .
She also starred in When We Rise .